{
  "text": "Prostaglandins E 2 and E 3 (PGE 2 and PGE 3 ), were extracted according to the previously published method from Yang et al. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, an aliquot of the 0.5 mL of PBS buffer was added to the frozen tissue or cell pellets, followed by homogenization in 1.5 mL tubes with ceramic beads using the Precellys tissue homogenizer (Bertin Technologies) and 400 mL aliquots were used for prostaglandin extraction. All extraction procedures were performed under minimal light. Samples were then reconstituted in 100 mL of methanol/0.1% acetic acid (50:50, v/v) prior to analysis by LC-MS/MS [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2142166",
